  "doc_id": "10126",
  "text": "The importance of writing the quantum statistical relation in terms of E and Φ G comes from the fact that E and Φ G (and not Q ∂T and I E ), which are the only two quantities that we need to compute on the boundary (N and J can be computed as surface integrals over the spatial sections of the horizon), are each independent of the choice of representative of the conformal boundary metric. Hence (98) is form invariant under PBH transformations that preserve the three boundary Killing vectors ∂ T , ∂ V and ∂ ψ [CITATION_1] . The thermodynamics of (60) and (62) can be obtained by applying the appropriate scaling limits to the thermodynamics of the MMT black hole.",
